default&#xa0;defaultThe Girls’ Attitudes Survey
defaultGirlguiding’s submission focuses 
defaulton evidence from the Girls’ Attitudes Surveys, our annual research into the opinions of girls and young women throughout the UK aged 11-21, described below (points 4-6). This evidence pr
defaultovides unique insight into why young women’s interest in STEM subjects may drop off. Girlguiding’s youth programmes offer a good practice example of how girls’ and young women’s interest in STEM subjects can be encouraged (points 21-22).
